Requirements
------------
The following software need to be installed on your machine

  - boost (version 1.33.1) 
	cmake will look in standard installation directories.
	If boost is installed in a non standard installation directory, this directory should be specified through BOOST_ROOT or BOOSTROOT:
	-DBOOST_ROOT=... in cmake command line.

  - lapack
	cmake will look in standard installation directories.

  - t3d or jrlMathTools (accessible through pkg-config)


Installation instructions for library MatrixAbstractLayer
---------------------------------------------------------


It is recommended to create a specific directory to install this package.
mkdir build
cd build
cmake [OPTIONS] -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX={installation directory} ..
make 
make install

[OPTION] (see also CMakeLists.txt)
-DSMALLMATRIX=t3d 
	if you want to use t3d for rigid-body transformations. 

-DSMALLMATRIX=jrlMathTools
	if you want to use jrlMathTools implementation for rigid-body transformations.

See also CMakeLists.txt for more information.


About cleaning and reinstalling
-------------------------------

in the build directory, cmake creates a CMakeCache.txt file to keep track of already installed files.
If you want to reinstall your package from scratch, it is recommended to remove this file first.
